[size=14pt][b][color=#FF00FF]CRITICAL DATA INTEGRITY FIX[/color][/b][/size]

This release addresses a [b][color=#FF0000]critical race condition[/color][/b] discovered during deep code analysis. The issue could cause [b]height pointer regression[/b] under concurrent write conditions - potentially orphaning blocks and creating database gaps.

[b]The Problem:[/b]
[code]Thread A: reads height pointer = 100
Thread B: reads height pointer = 100
Thread A: writes blocks 101-200, sets pointer = 200
Thread B: writes blocks 101-150, sets pointer = 150
RESULT: Pointer regresses from 200 to 150, blocks 151-200 become orphans![/code]

[b]The Solution:[/b]
[code]Thread A: acquires global_write_lock, writes 101-200, sets pointer = 200, releases
Thread B: acquires global_write_lock, reads pointer = 200, writes 201-250, releases
RESULT: All blocks contiguous, no data loss[/code]

[b][color=#00FF94]v2.2.0 introduces three critical fixes:[/color][/b]

[list]
[li][b]Global Write Lock Accessor[/b] - New [font=courier]acquire_global_write_lock()[/font] method for external code to safely coordinate writes[/li]
[li][b]TurboSync Legacy Mode Protection[/b] - All Transaction writes now acquire global lock first[/li]
[li][b]TOCTOU Race Elimination[/b] - Height pointer updates re-verify under lock to prevent time-of-check/time-of-use vulnerabilities[/li]
[/list]

