[size=16pt][b][color=#FFD700]12-WEEK OPTIMIZATION ROADMAP: MISSION CONTROL[/color][/b][/size]

We're launching an ambitious 12-week optimization program to achieve [b][color=#00FF94]100+ blocks per second sync[/color][/b] and [b][color=#00FF94]near-zero CPU overhead[/color][/b]. Each phase is named after orbital mechanics concepts - because we're going to the moon with engineering precision.

[center][size=14pt][b][color=#FF00FF]THE MISSION PHASES[/color][/b][/size][/center]

[hr]

[size=14pt][b][color=#00D9FF]PHASE 1: SCRAMJET (Week 1-2)[/color][/b][/size]
[i]High-speed atmospheric optimization - reduce drag, increase velocity[/i]

[b]Objectives:[/b]
[list]
[li][b]1.1 CBOR Response Serialization[/b] - Replace JSON with compact binary format[/li]
[li][b]1.2 LZ4 Standardization[/b] - Switch from zstd to ultra-fast LZ4 compression[/li]
[li][b]1.3 Decompression Parallelism Match[/b] - Parallel decode matching compression speed[/li]
[/list]

[b]Technical Details:[/b]
[code]Current State:
- JSON serialization: ~5ms per 10k blocks
- zstd compression: ~20ms at level 1
- Sequential decompression: single-threaded bottleneck

SCRAMJET Optimization:
- CBOR: 3x smaller than JSON, 5x faster to parse
- LZ4: 10x faster than zstd, 90% compression ratio
- Parallel decompress: utilize all CPU cores[/code]

[table]
[tr][td][b]Metric[/b][/td][td][b]Before[/b][/td][td][b]After[/b][/td][td][b]Improvement[/b][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Serialization[/td][td]5ms[/td][td]1ms[/td][td][color=#00FF94]5x faster[/color][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Compression[/td][td]20ms[/td][td]5ms[/td][td][color=#00FF94]4x faster[/color][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Bandwidth[/td][td]100%[/td][td]60%[/td][td][color=#00FF94]40% reduction[/color][/td][/tr]
[/table]

[b][color=#FFD700]Expected Result: 40% bandwidth reduction, 3x faster compression[/color][/b]

[hr]

[size=14pt][b][color=#00D9FF]PHASE 2: LAMINAR (Week 3-4)[/color][/b][/size]
[i]Smooth, turbulence-free flow - eliminate lock contention[/i]

[b]Objectives:[/b]
[list]
[li][b]2.1 DashMap Migration[/b] - Replace [font=courier]RwLock<HashMap>[/font] with lock-free [font=courier]DashMap[/font] for high-contention maps[/li]
[li][b]2.2 Tokio Mutex Migration[/b] - Replace [font=courier]std::sync::Mutex[/font] with [font=courier]tokio::sync::Mutex[/font] for async compatibility[/li]
[li][b]2.3 Batched spawn_blocking[/b] - Reduce thread pool overhead with batch operations[/li]
[/list]

[b]Technical Details:[/b]
[code]Lock Contention Analysis:
- Peer map: 10,000+ reads/sec, 100 writes/sec
- Block cache: 50,000+ reads/sec, 1,000 writes/sec
- Height pointer: 1,000+ reads/sec, 10 writes/sec

Current: RwLock causes reader starvation under write pressure
LAMINAR: DashMap allows concurrent readers during writes[/code]

[b]DashMap Performance:[/b]
[table]
[tr][td][b]Operation[/b][/td][td][b]RwLock<HashMap>[/b][/td][td][b]DashMap[/b][/td][td][b]Improvement[/b][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Concurrent reads[/td][td]Blocked during write[/td][td]Never blocked[/td][td][color=#00FF94]Lock-free[/color][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Write latency[/td][td]50-100us[/td][td]1-5us[/td][td][color=#00FF94]20x faster[/color][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Throughput[/td][td]100k ops/s[/td][td]10M ops/s[/td][td][color=#00FF94]100x higher[/color][/td][/tr]
[/table]

[b][color=#FFD700]Expected Result: 20-30% throughput increase[/color][/b]

[hr]

[size=14pt][b][color=#00D9FF]PHASE 3: HOHMANN (Week 5-6)[/color][/b][/size]
[i]Optimal transfer orbit - minimum energy, maximum efficiency[/i]

[b]Objectives:[/b]
[list]
[li][b]3.1 Header-First Staged Sync[/b] - Download block headers first, validate chain, then fetch bodies[/li]
[li][b]3.2 Checkpoint Jump Points[/b] - Pre-verified checkpoints every 100k blocks for instant sync start[/li]
[/list]

[b]Technical Details:[/b]
[code]Traditional Sync (current):
1. Request full blocks 1-1000
2. Validate each block fully
3. Request blocks 1001-2000
4. Repeat... (hours to sync 1M blocks)

HOHMANN Header-First Sync:
1. Download all headers (1M headers = 50MB, takes 10 seconds)
2. Verify header chain (PoW/signatures, takes 5 seconds)
3. Jump to checkpoint at block 900,000
4. Download only 100,000 blocks of bodies
5. Full sync in MINUTES, not hours![/code]

[b]Checkpoint Format:[/b]
[code]{
  "height": 900000,
  "block_hash": "0x7f3a...",
  "state_root": "0x9b2c...",
  "utxo_commitment": "0x4d8e...",
  "signatures": [
    {"validator": "0x...", "sig": "0x..."},
    // 67%+ of validators signed
  ]
}[/code]

[b][color=#FFD700]Expected Result: Initial sync from hours to minutes[/color][/b]

[hr]

[size=14pt][b][color=#00D9FF]PHASE 4: SLINGSHOT (Week 7-8)[/color][/b][/size]
[i]Gravity assist acceleration - use existing momentum[/i]

[b]Objectives:[/b]
[list]
[li][b]4.1 Hot Cache Peer Selection[/b] - Prefer peers that recently served the block range you need[/li]
[li][b]4.2 Continuous Stream Protocol[/b] - Keep connection open, stream blocks without per-request overhead[/li]
[/list]

[b]Technical Details:[/b]
[code]Current Peer Selection:
- Round-robin across all peers
- No memory of what peer served what blocks
- Cache miss rate: 60-80%

SLINGSHOT Hot Cache Selection:
- Track last 10 block ranges served by each peer
- Prefer peer whose cache contains your requested range
- Cache hit rate: 90%+[/code]

[b]Continuous Stream Protocol:[/b]
[code]Current (request-response):
Request 1 → [network latency] → Response 1
Request 2 → [network latency] → Response 2
Request 3 → [network latency] → Response 3
Overhead: 3x network round-trips

SLINGSHOT (streaming):
Stream request (1-1000) →
  Block 1 → Block 2 → Block 3 → ... → Block 1000
Overhead: 1x network round-trip for 1000 blocks![/code]

[b][color=#FFD700]Expected Result: 3-5x cache hit improvement[/color][/b]

[hr]

[size=14pt][b][color=#00D9FF]PHASE 5: KALMAN (Week 9-10)[/color][/b][/size]
[i]Optimal state estimation - predict and adapt in real-time[/i]

[b]Objectives:[/b]
[list]
[li][b]5.1 PID Rate Controller[/b] - Proportional-Integral-Derivative control for request rate[/li]
[li][b]5.2 Kalman Network Predictor[/b] - Predict peer latency and adjust proactively[/li]
[/list]

[b]Technical Details:[/b]
[code]PID Controller for Sync Rate:
- Setpoint: Target 50 blocks/s
- P (Proportional): Increase rate when below target
- I (Integral): Correct persistent undershoot
- D (Derivative): Dampen oscillations

Kalman Filter for Latency:
- State: [estimated_latency, latency_trend]
- Measurement: actual_round_trip_time
- Prediction: next_expected_latency
- Adaptation: pre-adjust request timing[/code]

[b]Self-Tuning Parameters:[/b]
[table]
[tr][td][b]Parameter[/b][/td][td][b]Manual Tuning[/b][/td][td][b]Kalman Auto-Tune[/b][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Request batch size[/td][td]Fixed 10,000[/td][td]Dynamic 1k-100k[/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Timeout duration[/td][td]Fixed 30s[/td][td]Dynamic 2x predicted RTT[/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Concurrent requests[/td][td]Fixed 3[/td][td]Dynamic 1-10 based on bandwidth[/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Compression level[/td][td]Fixed level 1[/td][td]Dynamic based on CPU/bandwidth ratio[/td][/tr]
[/table]

[b][color=#FFD700]Expected Result: Self-tuning optimal parameters for any network condition[/color][/b]

[hr]

[size=14pt][b][color=#00D9FF]PHASE 6: DELTA-V (Week 11-12)[/color][/b][/size]
[i]Maximum velocity change - final burn to orbit[/i]

[b]Objectives:[/b]
[list]
[li][b]6.1 Rkyv Zero-Copy Integration[/b] - Deserialize directly from network buffer without allocation[/li]
[li][b]6.2 Pre-Compressed Storage[/b] - Store blocks already compressed, skip compression on sync[/li]
[li][b]6.3 io_uring Integration[/b] - Linux kernel async I/O for maximum disk throughput[/li]
[/list]

[b]Technical Details:[/b]
[code]Rkyv Zero-Copy:
- Traditional: Network buffer → Deserialize → Allocate → Copy → Process
- Rkyv: Network buffer → Cast pointer → Process (NO COPY!)
- Memory savings: 50% reduction
- Speed improvement: 10x faster deserialization

Pre-Compressed Storage:
- Current: Decompress → Process → Compress → Store
- DELTA-V: Store compressed → Serve compressed → Decompress only on read
- CPU savings: 2x compression removed from hot path

io_uring:
- Traditional: syscall per I/O operation (expensive context switch)
- io_uring: Batch 1000s of I/O ops in single syscall
- Throughput: 1M IOPS vs 100k IOPS[/code]

[b]Final Performance Target:[/b]
[table]
[tr][td][b]Metric[/b][/td][td][b]v2.2.0[/b][/td][td][b]After DELTA-V[/b][/td][td][b]Improvement[/b][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Sync speed[/td][td]12 blocks/s[/td][td]100+ blocks/s[/td][td][color=#00FF94]8x faster[/color][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]CPU usage[/td][td]60%[/td][td]10%[/td][td][color=#00FF94]6x lower[/color][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Memory usage[/td][td]500MB[/td][td]250MB[/td][td][color=#00FF94]50% reduction[/color][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]I/O latency[/td][td]1ms[/td][td]0.1ms[/td][td][color=#00FF94]10x faster[/color][/td][/tr]
[/table]

[b][color=#FFD700]Expected Result: Near-zero CPU overhead for I/O operations[/color][/b]

